1. Screen Scraping Methods
Screen scraping is used for UI elements that don't have a clear "data" structure.

Common Initial Steps:
Open UiPath Studio and create a Blank Process.
On the Design tab (Top Ribbon), click the Screen Scraping icon.
Use the mouse to click the application or window you want to scrape. This opens the Screen Scraper Wizard.


a. Full Text
Best for: High-speed extraction; can read hidden text.
Step: In the Wizard’s Scraping Method dropdown (right side), select Full Text.
Note: This is the default method. It captures the text but ignores the formatting/layout.

Finish: Click Finish. UiPath generates a sequence with a Get Full Text activity.

b. Native
Best for: Extracting text from applications that use GDI (like Notepad or older Windows apps); preserves text position.
Step: Change the dropdown to Native.
Options: Check No Formatting if you only want the raw text, or leave it unchecked to keep the relative positions of the words.
Finish: Click Finish. UiPath generates a Get Visible Text activity.

c. OCR (Optical Character Recognition)
Best for: Scanned documents, virtual machines (Citrix/RDP), or images where text is not selectable.
Step: Select OCR in the dropdown.
Engine: Choose an OCR Engine (e.g., Tesseract OCR or UiPath Screen OCR).
Finish: Click Finish. This creates a Get OCR Text activity with the chosen engine inside it.

2. Data Scraping & Variable Display
Data Scraping is used specifically for structured data like tables, lists, or search results on a webpage.
Demonstrate Data Scraping (Web Page):
Open a browser (e.g., a search results page on Google or Amazon).

Click the Table Extraction (Modern) or Data Scraping (Classic) icon in the Ribbon.
Indicate: Select the first element (e.g., the name of a product).

Pattern: Select a similar second element (the wizard will automatically identify the entire list).
Rename: Rename the column (e.g., "Product Name") and click Next.
Extract Correlated Data: Click "Extract Correlated Data" to pick another field, like "Price".
Output: Click Finish. It will generate an Extract Structured Data activity and store results in a variable called ExtractDataTable.

Display in Message Box:

Drag an Output Data Table activity. Set input to ExtractDataTable and create a string variable dtString (Ctrl+K).
Drag a Message Box and input dtString.
